description: Ahead of the fourth phase of polling in the Uttar Pradesh Assembly election, which is scheduled to take place on February 23, leaders including Amit Shah, Akhilesh Yadav, Arvind Kejriwal and CM Yogi Adityanath addressed public meetings in the state on Monday. Meanwhile, Congress leader Rahul Gandhi addressed a rally in Manipur’s Imphal. Assembly elections in five states – Punjab, Uttar Pradesh, Uttarakhand, Goa and Manipur – are being held in February and March. Follow IndiaToday.in for LIVE updates.
